4.55/5  rDev +0.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5Thanks to Outdoor7or24 for the gift of this exceptional brew! Pours a medium amber producing 3 full fingers of frothy, beige, variously bubbled, frothy head that leaves rings & webs of soapy lacing. Aroma citrusy lemon-orange & piney hops backed by sweet & thick caramel malt. Taste is a huge citrus juice/peel & pine bitter hoppiness! Which subdues & overruns the sweet caramel malt of the nose. There's a toasty buttered breadiness & tropical fruitness in the background. Huge hop bite & bitterness from start through aftertaste that intensifies from mid-sip into initial aftertaste. More like an IPA than a PA. There is something in both the nose & the mouth that is onion like, not off putting at all, but different. Mouthfeel is light to medium bodied, juciy throughout, peppery & creamy in the finish. It is difficult for me to believe that this is a 60 IBU brew, the bitterness seems higher than that. But what the hey, I'm a hophead at heart. 950 charactersmothmanscott, Nov 13, 2016
