4.5/5  rDev -0.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.517 days old poured from a 12 oz bottle.  Pours golden amber color with minimal white head which quickly disappeared leaving minimal lacing.  The smell is strong citrus (mostly orange) and hops, as would be expected from a citra-hopped APA.  This borders the edge of an IPA, but it's done brilliantly. The mouthfeel is strong carbonation but smooth.  The taste is all citrus, orange,and hops with almost no lasting bitterness but a good malt balance on the back end.  This is an outstanding beer that would be a daily drinker for me if I had access to it. 554 charactersjvgoor3786, May 23, 2016
4.27/5  rDev -5.7%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25I'm not a big fan of pale ale's but, I saw this recently on tap at a growler bar and thought I would see what all the hype was about.
L- Poured into a 16 oz. Pint glass, looks like a typical pale ale. Hazy, light orange, with a foamy head and good lacing.
S- All of these pale ales smell similar to me, this one is no different. Hoppy, citrus, and grapefruit smell.
T- Taste follows the nose, hoppy with a very good balance. Not overly bitter, but it's there. 
F- Pretty heavy, took me a while to finish.
O- Well, this was about what I expected for the style. I don't prefer this type, but I can see why it is popular. Thought this was an excellent pale ale, one of the better ones I've had. If you haven't had a chance to try it, check it out, it's worthy of the hype! Highly recommended! 790 charactersdcjones82, May 23, 2016
