4.83/5  rDev +6.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5All around, Zombie Dust is an exceptional American Pale Ale, showcasing the best of the Citra Hop.  While TG's Psuedosue is very similar and even has a little more complexity of taste than it (have done side-by-sides numerous times), Zombie Dust always takes the cake with its balance, approachability and citrusy goodness.  
While it remains my favorite APA and even IPA (lines are blurred a bit with ZD), it needs to be enjoyed fresh as the smell/taste fades quickly and becomes almost a different beer after 4 weeks.  This is my only knock on it. Usually not a problem at retail as these brews move quickly. 611 charactersRBMurphy4, Dec 23, 2015
