4.15/5  rDev -8.4%look: 3.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.259-16-2015 on the bottle.
A - Nice burnt orange colour. Hazy. One finger of white head on top. Mild carbonation. Spotty lace and a film of retention. 
S - Melon, pineapple, passionfruit. Smells like citra! A little grass. Sweet fruit. 
T - Mild alcohol note, citra all over the place. More pineapple and passionfruit, earthy and grassy too. Citrusy zip. The bitterness is a really nice drying note that isn't always done so subtly, yet intensely. 
M - Medium body, good sharp bitterness and a mild carbonation. 
O/D - This isn't mind blowing. It's a pale ale with a ton of citra in it. It's damn good, but I'm not gonna blow a load over it like so many others. Tasty stuff and very sessionable, just not jaw dropping. Also, a pale ale shouldn't have 60 IBUs and I don't understand why this is recognized as such. 816 charactersbylerteck, Oct 04, 2015
