4.68/5  rDev +3.3%look: 4.25 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Where to begin on this one. This being one of my first adventure into beer reviewing I will try to avoid butchering it. This APA pours a radiant hazy orange color with a finger head that leaves nice tracing the way down. The smell (my favorite part) hits you with an a one two with sweet malts and tropical fruit. The taste matches the smell very well but is followed up with a hint of bitterness. It has a superb mouth feel that balances a full body flavor and retains its refreshing qualities. My overall opinion on this beer is obviously 3 floyds has knocked it out of the park again. This is one of the best APAs in the business. There may be some that are better out there but this is definitely top 3. 707 charactersMikeCooke, Aug 27, 2015
