5/5  rDev +10.4%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Poured from the bottle into a Sixpoint Teku.
Look - Pours a beautiful burnt orange, almost amber color. Forms a light fluffy head, and the lacing remains on the glass.
Smell - Citrus and pine.
Taste - The citrus hits hard up front, but there is a strong malt background that really rounds off the flavors nicely. Pine and hops on the back end as you swallow with just the right amount of bitterness.
Mouthfeel - Bready, medium-bodied, perfect carbonation, and smooth.
Overall - My favorite pale ale to date! I really enjoy the citra hop, and 3 Floyd's really did a good job incorporating it into their recipe. If you haven't had it, please do so. I gave it a 5/5 for a reason! 681 charactersSad_Larry, May 06, 2015
