4.43/5  rDev -2.2%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5My brother brings this over as an extra he scored in a trade. This has been a long time want for me just because of the hype surrounding it. Relatively fresh bottle as I am told.
A: Hazy mellow gold with nice retention of foamy lacing on the glass. Very interesting a pretty for a pale ale.
S: Very interesting blend of the hop character with the base malts. Good amount of lemon hop sweetness and some other citrus notes. 
T: Very interesting indeed. Opens up with a good non-assertive hop blend finishing out with strong honey notes. A bit of grapefruit and other citrus tones. It is a beer that I am savoring and really can't see myself just kicking this back.
M: Follows through excellently with the taste. The bitterness from the hop character is subdued and you the malts are constrained well as to not give off that somewhat lager-ish overly malty and sometimes copper taste that you can get from pale ales.
O: A great take on a pale ale and I would seek this out again. I can't put this ahead of Hoppy Birthday just because of my love for IPAs but this is definitely in the top 3 pale ales I've ever had. 1,117 charactersputonyourwalkingshoes, Apr 08, 2015
