4.43/5  rDev -2.2%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5JKali860, Apr 07, 2015
4.43/5  rDev -2.2%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5chibanaryan, Apr 07, 2015
5/5  rDev +10.4%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 512 oz. bottle poured into a snifter
Pours a hazy, deep straw gold with two fingers of fluffy white head that maintains a thin cap and soft fuzzy lacing on the side of my glass. Aroma is a captivating blend of bright citrus that takes my nose hostage the instant I pop the cap. Lots of lemon zest, grapefruit, and lime with just a touch of sweet biscuity malt. I'm tempted to splash some on my neck as cologne. That's as sexy as any pale ale can smell.
Tastes every bit as good as my nose told me it would. More sharp, bright citrus that manages to both bite the palate and gently caress it at the same time. Impressive multitasking. There's faint tropical fruit and floral notes, but lemon, orange, and grapefruit rule the day. Also a hint of pine resin for good measure. Just as in the aroma, the light grainy malt offers just enough body to give a fleeting illusion of sweetness. Body is a bit lighter than medium, with lively carbonation. Crisp and refreshing, with a slightly dry finish and lingering memories of all the hop goodness within.
I was worried my anticipation would lead to a classic case of unmet expectations. Nope. I waited until the last bottle of my 6-pack to review it, as I didn't want to let my initial euphoria influence my rating unjustly. Pale ale, IPA, call it whatever you want. This beer is a work of art in every way. I wanted to find a reason not to rate it a 5, but I'd be lying to myself. 1,425 charactersglass_house, Apr 07, 2015
