4.45/5  rDev -1.8%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5Poured cold into a tulip glass.  Bottled date of 5/7/14 drinking on 5/26.
Look = 4.5 Pours a cloudy golden copper with a hint of orange.  Three fingers of crisp white head fades to a thin ring.  Lace is nuts; super dense small bubbles and incredibly sticky.
Smell = 4.5  Citra hops all around.  Citrus and tropical fruits, earthy, grass and pine.  Super strong.  Even better as it warms up.  A hint of sweetness.
Taste = 4.5  Citrus, grassy, grainy hops dominate.  A hint of sweetness with a bitter finish.  No hint of alcohol.  Hop dominated but a little balance fits the APA style perfectly.
Feel = 4.0  Medium body, medium-to-high carbonation.  Fits the crispness of the flavor well.
Drinkability = 5.0  Not sure if I’ve ever had a more drinkable beer.  6.4% but smooth as can be.  Hops dominated but fantastically refreshing.  If it wasn’t so hard to get I’d drink 4 at a time.  Flexible too; refreshing during the summer but complex for a cold winter’s night.
Overall = 4.475  Very well rounded APA; hop focused but complex and even a little balanced at the same time.  Pretty, great smell, great taste, refreshing, everything you could ask for. 1,158 characterskbwalters, Apr 04, 2015
