4.77/5  rDev +5.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Some have said this beer is overrated and maybe it is, but that doesn't mean it isn't a fantastic brew. 
A- slightly cloudy, orange haze, and off white head with very good lacing
S- Fantastic mix of orange peel, citrus, and pine    jump from the glass while a subtle malt sweetness is also apparent
T- Solid malt backbone with a crisp cracker taste dominating; Citra hops create a fruity bitter taste that is very prominent but not overpowering
M- Medium, light body with a crisp dry finish. Medium carbonation that leaves some hop taste on the palate for minutes after drinking.
O- Overall, a very good beer. Although I think it may not be so popular if it were readily available, it is still one of my favorite beers. It is hoppy enough for hopheads, yet balanced and smooth enough to be a session beer (but too damn rare).  I will definitely keep my eyes open for more. 876 charactersHoosierCountry, Mar 16, 2015
