4.78/5  rDev +5.5%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 5Poured into a Duvel snifter glass.
A - Poured a dark honey color, formed a finger of dense and creamy, slightly off-white head.
S - Amazing. Oranges, hops, grapefruit, apples, pineapple, mango, peach, persimmons. One of the most bright, vibrant and tropical aroma's I've ever smelled on a beer.
T - Very similar to the nose, but not as sweet, more like the savory side of these fruits. I would have preferred these tastes be just slightly sweeter, but the taste is amazing regardless.
O - This beer isn't just hype, it really is great. for me, the beer would be a perfect 100 had the taste matched the aroma's sweetness just a bit more, but as it stands it is still an A+ beer in my books. Definitely the best pale ale I've ever had and I highly recommend it.
V - The value is good because if you've got it in your hands, you probably had to work for it, thus you're probably willing to pay whatever price tag is on it. Seriously though, it is worth every penny. 963 charactersBeer-Revelry, Jan 11, 2015
