4.67/5  rDev +3.1%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5A: Beautiful beer, clear orange amber with perfect white head retained well, and excellent lacing down.
S: Very tropical smell. Lots of fruits mango, citrus. Followed by a more floral hop and piney smell. Smell wasn't very strong however.
T: Amazing. incredibly well balanced and delicious. Very "juciy" lots of citrus and troipical fruits but its amazing how well its balanced and how easy it is to drink. There's a very slight grapefruit/ hop bitterness, but there also a semi sweet malt to it. All meshed with the fruits. And that great hop aftertaste. Its  Amazing. No alcohol presence at all. Only slight downside is I wish the flavors were a little stronger.
F: Spot On. Very refreshing perfect carbonation. And perfect balance just like the taste. Not sticky or dry.
O: Little different from my normal Ipas. But an amazing beer. One of my top 3 easily. Super easy to drink and so juicy. 894 charactersGinjaSlice, Dec 25, 2014
