5/5  rDev +10.4%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Tried not to be biased in my review, but this beer is just that damn good.  It fulfilled my expectations and then some.  Here goes:
A:  As I've said in other review, FFF has got the appearances of its beers down to a T.  Beautiful, clear orange with a ton of carbonation bursting forth from the bottom of the glass.  This beer also has a massive, three-fingered head that leaves a ton of lacing.
S:  Beautiful - but not overbearing - collection of tropical fruit owing to the citra hops.  Mango, pineapple, grass, lemon and grapefruit - they're all here.  Also lots of caramel malt.
T:  To die for.  Caramel malt gives way to the hops - perfectly balanced, like an APA should be.  Hop tastes follow the nose - just splendid.
M:  Plenty of carbonation, medium-bodied as well.  Outstanding.
O:  Deserves its place at the top of the APA list. 844 charactersleantom, Nov 28, 2014
