A. Pours a hazy amber/copper color with a beautiful foamy 1 1/4" head.
S. A slight bread smell overshadowed by a fruit bucket of well picked hops. Makes you want to drink it. 
T. What a great balance of flavors.  Some biscuity maltyness with a great amount of fruity citrusy hop flavor and a little bit of white grape. Perfect amount of bitterness compliments this excellently balanced but also complex flavor.  Aftertaste is like cotton candy. 
M. Medium bodied with some prickly mouth carbonation that slightly follows down the throat. Just what I want out of an IPA/APA. 
