4.77/5  rDev +5.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.7512 oz bottle poured into an IPA glass.  Bottled 10/09/2014.
Pours a clear gold color with lots of tiny bubbles and an enormous white head.  Good lacing and retention.
Smells like heaven!  This is the stuff dreams are made of...  At least mine.  Loads of lemony citrus with some tangerine and grapefruit.
The flavor is just as I had hoped.  Lots of citrus and tropical fruit up front with just a hint of sweetness from the malt before the hops take over again for the finish.
Medium body with a dry finish and a nice lingering bitterness.
Overall, an outstanding beer. I don't know if it's an APA or and IPA, but I don't really care.  What it is is an amazingly well crafted beer with about as perfect of balance as I can imagine.  I would happily drink this again (and again and again). 788 charactersmr-jj, Oct 28, 2014
