4.75/5  rDev +4.9%Look: Crystal clear golden amber with a nice white head. Lots of legs keep the head up and some lacing. 
Smell: Citra hops come bursting out of the bottle with hints of lemon, line, kiwi, mango, pineapple, and a slight earthy hop finish. The malt makes a slight appearance in the background with a nice bready malt but the hops are definitely the show stealer here! 
Taste: Wow! For how hoppy the nose was it is amazingly balanced on the tongue! Getting lemon, lime, mango, slight peach, definitely piney, the sweet malt starts to take over but before it does some sweet orange and a dash more pine hit the tongue before the sweet malt takes over in what can only be described as a perfect balance. There is some lingering pine and mango notes of the finish that buzz on the tongue long after each sip. 
Mouthfeel: Dank is the best way to describe this beer. It's wet and quenching at first but the hops quickly suck up the moisture after you've gotten just enough to leave the pine and citrus fruits dancing on your palate begging you to taste another sip
. Outstanding. Overall: Wow! Just one outstanding brew! This is one of those rare ones that lives up to and surpasses the hype. It's dank and hoppy yet sweet and balanced while drying out to allow you time to reflect on just how well the brew is crafted. I could drink this like water if I wasn't careful! I wasn't impressed with everything I've had from three Floyd's so far but this one killed it! The king of APA in my opinion. 1,491 charactersBergBeer, Oct 15, 2014
