4.77/5  rDev +5.3%Enjoyed this beer on tap at Hopleaf in Chicago.  Poured into a Hopleaf pint glass, the brew is a lovely, clear copper with about a pinkie finger of head that seems long-lasting. Leaves lacing down the glass.
The aroma is big grapefruit, tropical  fruits, some lemon and a tease of malty sweetness in the back.
This beer tastes great. Lots of citrus and tropical fruit notes, a hint of grassiness and lemongrass perhaps. Some pine notes come out to play and there is a pleasant and lingering bitterness as well. As it warmed a bit, perhaps a little cracker on the tongue as well. But the hops dominate with their tropical fruit salad of fun.
Very nice, medium body and smooth on the palate.
Overall, great to finally have this beer. It lived up to the hype. So tasty and so drinkable. Great stuff! 796 charactersSD-Alefan, Oct 14, 2014
