4.48/5  rDev -1.1%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Enjoyed on tap in a straight pint glass. 
A- Light copper, high degree of clarity, one finger of white head. 
S- Lots of papaya, mango, and pineapple, and citrus. Not much else really just a huge hop presence. 
T- Light sweetness, fruity flavors of tropical fruits, some light bitterness on the end with some light toasted malt. 
M- Medium, really easy drinking. Not watery at all. 
O- This is an amazing beer that really straddles that APA/IPA line. This is the best showcase of Citra hops that I have encountered. Thirsty Dog's Citra Dog and Odd Side's CPA try to imitate but don't even come close. Really tried to go in not expecting to be blown away and I would suggest everyone try to do that. It's not a DIPA but just a very aromatic and full hop flavored pale ale that you could drink all day and not get sick of. Definitely worth a drive for your 2 case limit. 873 charactersPaulyB83, Sep 27, 2014
