4.25/5  rDev -6.2%A:  Pours a nice anger/ orange color with some haze.  Forms a full white head that slowly dies.  Lots and lots of lacing in this beer. 
S:  You can smell this beer from a foot away and it smells great.  Floral hops, citrus, lemon zest.  In the background is some pine, grass and malt.   The floral hop aroma is really outstanding.
T:  The citrus/ floral hop flavors hit first with a dry bitterness to the finish.  Some pine and hay flavors present even stronger than in the smell.  This beer is a study of balance and contrast.  
I enjoyed this beer more once it warmed up and the flavors became more pronounced.  I usually drink pale ales cold, but this one is good enough to enjoy at cellar temperature.
M:  Nicely carbonated as benefits the style.  Fuller bodied than most pale ales, the very dry finish leaves you wanting more.  
O:  This is a quality beer.  The hype may have exceeded what you get in this beer, but you will not regret giving it a try.  Not overly complex, but very flavorful for the style and very nicely balanced.  An enjoyable drinking experience. 1,076 charactersimscotty, Sep 24, 2014
