4.75/5  rDev +4.9%Poured from bottle into snifter.
A- Nice light hay color with a touch of amber.  Decent carbonation, small half finger head and medium lacing.
S-  Lots of fruitiness up front.  Grapefruit, mango, pear and other citrus smells with just a little floral notes.
T- Fresh citrus and floral notes.  Just a little malt and pine in the aftertaste.  Nice mix of hops and very smooth and drinkable.  As the beer warmed up there were light notes of vanilla in the finish.
M- Light and smooth body.  As mentioned, this is a crisp and refreshing IPA and that is very noticeable on the palate.
O-  Definitely gives other top IPAs a run for their money.  One of the better ones I've encountered and I will be trading more NE brews for these guys again in the future.  Three Floyds is truly a brewery to be reckoned with and hit the nail on the head with this one. 855 charactersEveningCordial, Sep 07, 2014
