4.43/5  rDev -2.2%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.512oz from a buddy... Poured into a tulip glass -
A: cloudy, hazed orange; about a finger of bubbly, cream head forms on the pour and leaves some impressive rings of thick, sugary lace; impressive look for a pale ale.
S: citrus hops; orange / apricot pith; tangerine; a tad peppery; some light bready notes are there in the background.
T: such a smooth blend of flavor... a mix of citrus and tropical fruit hop flavor; just a touch of bread crust malt; just a bit chalky, too; seems like some sort of nuanced Belgian twist is in there, too; pretty complex for the style; very tasty.
M: medium body; high carbonation; pretty lively and refreshing.
O: one of the best pale ales around; nice and hoppy, but also with some other light (and unique) components in the aroma and taste; on top of that, it's very drinkable! 819 charactersjpro, Aug 13, 2014
