4.89/5  rDev +7.9%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75poured from draft into a pint glass
A - Perfectly clear orange hue. Decent head and retention. Didn't really pay much attention to this; was too excited to try!
S - God. Damn. What a brew. This thing is just gushing like they say, with grapefruit, pineapple, peach, mango, all sorts of tropical fruits. Some bread and biscuit comes through from the malts as well, but definitely in the background.
T - Nearly as amazing as the aroma, with all of the same flavors. I get more bready malt flavor than I did with PseudoSue, which is not my preference when it comes to pale ales and IPAs for the most part. Bitterness is quite tame, but for a pale ale, I can see why people might think it's closer to an IPA.
M - Light to medium bodied, but it goes down quite nicely with just the right amount of carbonation and texture. Can seem a little watery at times.
O - The best beer I had at FFF. Really neck and neck with Toppling Goliath's PseudoSue. The only thing I can say is that Zombie Dust has the better aroma, while PseudoSue has the better flavor. Hope to get around to this again! 1,085 charactersDemoniChris, Jul 06, 2014
