4.18/5  rDev -7.7%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4Decided to try this because of all the very high recommendations and it's scarcity makes it that much more exciting.
A - Beautiful pale orange color with superior white head that sticks around. Good lacing for the most part. Very clear. Pours thick for an APA.
S - Great hoppy fragrance with a floral/citrus character that shines through. Has a dank hop character with some grassy notes. Very hop centered without much malt or alcohol in the nose. 
T - Has all the hops from the aroma with all the hoppiness . The front also has a sweetness from the malt to compliment the hop bitterness. Nice smooth finish with a medium bitterness from the hops. The last flavors on the palate are some sweet and delicious hops.
M - Medium mouth-feel. Has a nice bitterness that lightly sits on the back of the tongue. Fine carbonation.
Overall, this is an IPA and the only reason it's called an APA is because of the shadow Permanent Funeral and APW put it under. It's a great beer that has all of the citra hops you can sink your teeth into. I love the citrus hops and the body make it very drinkable. Perfect if you don't like overly bitter IPA's but would like a more citrus/hoppy pale ale. I could drink these for ever.
Glass type: Tulip 1,233 charactersdmgeng, Jul 01, 2014
