T-A trio of bitterness hits the palate at first. Hops, citrus, and pine make up the front of the palate but do not overwhelm. The aforementioned notes blend perfectly with the sweet honey and flowers (maybe jasmine or calendula). Finishes with a nice, spicy bite
MF-Crisp and medium-bodied. Fells nice and thick for an APA. 
O-Damn good pale ale. I feel like so many more APA and pale ales are coming out now that this one is losing its prestige, but it's still a phenomenal brew. It's essentially everything a pale ale should be. 784 charactersJacurdy60, Jun 11, 2014
