4.44/5  rDev -2%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Bottle is about a month and a half old. Great extra from a trade that I am very appreciative of.
Pours out a dark orange in color with no translucence. Nice white, one-finger head with decent retention and some nice lacing.
Smell is fruity mango, orange, pineapple as one would expect from Citra hops. There is a TINY bit of bitterness in the background that is very hard to notice. Definitely some nice sweet malts in the background.
Taste is a tiny bit more bitter but the prized fruits mentioned above come through and shine with the sweetness of the malts. Very well balanced.
Mouthfeel is fairly thick for the style due to the carbonation which I really like.
Overall I always love Zombie Dust and plan on trying to trade for a couple fresh 6 packs. Really a well put together beer that is even better on tap. When this stuff is even more fresh it is one of my favorites and a perpetual want. 902 charactersTheBeerDrinker, May 04, 2014
