4.35/5  rDev -4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5A- clean, deep gold but not quite amber. 1 finger white head. Very clean looking. Just how a pale should look.
S- Citra hops explode out of the glass. I am a sucker for this hop and the ZD does an outstanding job of highlighting the aroma of it. Sweet caramel notes in the background.
T- Layers of flavors, especially at this low of an ABV. An elaborate hop profile balanced with a chewy, caramel candy smoothness. Bright flavors of pineapple, mango, and papaya. Some hoppy pales and IPAs fail to generate a true balance and continuity, but no such problem here.
M- Crisp, yet creamy. Mid body. Intense bitterness that lingers. 
O- There are very few beers that can bring such an intense, aggressive, and tantalizing hop level cascading throughout each sip and still find a way to make it smooth. FFF is rare to disappoint. ZD is right there with Dreadnaught in my opinion. 877 charactersBosoxfan20, Feb 26, 2014
