Smell: Citra hop fruit profile jumps out right away. Tropical fruits of mangos, pineapple, kiwi, tangerines, and orange peel. A nutty malt profile with accents of caramel and light oak as well. 
Taste: Pleasant malty front filled with peanuts, caramel, slight molasses, and oak. Hop body comes shortly after providing a bright, sweet hop profile with Citra accents all over it. Some light hop bitterness mixes well with fruity and malt tones. Oranges, lemon, lime, kiwi, and pineapple dance on the palate for a long time after drinking. 
Mouthfeel: Incredibly drinkable, smooth malt mixes very well with the hoppiness of this brew. 
Overall: This is a great brew but I don't think it is world class. I've had it a few times, on draft and in bottle to make sure I wasn't missing anything before I reviewed it. No doubt that is beer is a must try though, really enjoyed the six pack I was able to get. 1,110 charactersKFBR392, Nov 26, 2013
