4.77/5  rDev +5.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75A - Slightly cloudy golden orange, with a full, pillowy head of off-white. The head fades slowly, and lacing is extensive and persistent.
S - A big, fat blast of hop power, with citrus rind and grass out front, pine and resin underneath, with a wildness that ranges around.
T - Following the nose, but with a malt complement that highlights the wonderful peach elements and offers sweetness.  There is a quick, cascading turn, a smack of citrus, mostly grapefruit. Coming in next is a tart and bitter snap, that closes with a chewy, pith-heavy bitterness.
M - A light drink with decent carbonation, but the chewiness of the hop oils does build.  If I ever had more than one Zombie Dust, I might still stop with one.
O - I cannot think of another beer quite like Zombie Dust. It may be an APA, and its light feel going down emphasizes this, but its clear hop focus and robust fruit and bitter has more in common with IPAs than with the typical APAs I've enjoyed.  I find Zombie Dust to be a pleasure, and I love the full frontal attack of the fruit and pine that is at this beer's core.  It drops off quickly, so don't leave this one sitting around for long, drink it up and enjoy. 1,184 charactersTsar_Riga, Nov 09, 2013
