4.35/5  rDev -4%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Special thanks to Phyl21ca for sending us this out west.
A: A full 2 fingers of soapy white head top a hazy golden amber ale. A few meandering bubbles of carbonation make a break for the top. 
S: Sweet pine resin mixed with notes of grapefruit pith. Floral notes up front of sweet flowers and tropical fruits, pineapple and mango and bitter orange. 
T: Orange bitters up front pop on the palette. Sweet malts follow and support the bitters with a malty profile. A solid pine resin is there but not overwhelming, like a balancing act of malts, pine resin and orange bitters. Sweet tropical fruit juice is also present, maybe mango or pineapple. 
M: A thicker mouth feel, nearly syrupy and coats the mouth well. Carbonation is medium with pin pricks that liven the tongue. 
O: Extremely well balanced without shying away from the big flavours. Enjoyed the combination of citrus, pine resin and tropical fruits with that backbone of malts. A highly drinkable and refreshing IPA that comes close to a DIPA. 1,007 charactersFondueVoodoo, Sep 03, 2013
