4.8/5  rDev +6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.75Big thanks to my buddy Andy for bringing me two
Of these and two gumballheads straight from the brewery.
A - Pours a very carbonated golden, orange looking brew. Bubbles all over the glass racing up to a thick, large bubbly off white head. Settles slowly with good lines of lacing everywhere. 
S - Whoa citra!! Big citra hop blast in the nose. A bit of pine sapp, and pine needles. I pick up some caramel malt in here for the balance. 
T - Yea citra hops are definitely the strong point in here. But there's also a juicy mango fruit flavor in here like biting into the ripe pulp itself. Delicious. Hops are slightly bitter but still very fresh in this. And some piney sapp in the nose is here in flavor combined with some caramel malt.
M - Light bodied brew with tickling high carbonation. Sweetness mixed with hops effortlessly throughout the mouth, and ever so easy going down. Incredibly quaffable.
O - This beer deserves any praise that it gets. Honestly the best of the "pale ale" category excluding the "I" by miles. I would drink this all day and would probably eat someone's brains if it meant getting this beer sent to PA. 1,136 charactershaazer, Aug 28, 2013
