4.47/5  rDev -1.3%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5355ml bottle
No bottle info!
Served chilled in an over sized wine glass.
Thanks to pittsburghkid66 for this amazing extra from the top of my want list! 
Appearance: Wow, quite a bit darker than I was expecting; this looks quite like an IPA. Lightly clouded apricot orange body topped by a good sized white head that displays reasonable retention and leaves good lace. 
Smell: I have no experience with Citra hops so this should be interesting. Wow, from the second the cap was cracked I could tell that this is going to be a great beer! The nose is all hops - Orange, grapefruit, mango, peach, under ripe guava (wtf!!!), mild pine, grass and a leafy herbal quality basically sums it up. Closer inspection reveals a very light caramel note. I know this is my first experience of Citra, but it is already up on my list of favorite hops! 
Taste: Hmmmm, this tastes quite like the single hop (Amarillo) IPA that I made last year... Maybe my true calling is as a brewer and not as a mathematician - well at least I hope it is!
The initial flavour is sweet malt, but this is quickly overrun by citrus, tropical fruit and strong grassy notes. Solid bitterness and lasting flavour. 
Mouthfeel: Bang on for the style; medium body, lightly oily with moderate level of carbonation. Easy drinking and super refreshing. 
Overall: Great beer, I would drink this throughout summer if I lived near FFF. One thing though; why do FFF bottle their huge IPA's like Apocalypse Cow in bombers and their refreshing pale ale in a 355ml? 1,518 charactersThehuntmaster, Dec 30, 2011
