S: This beer is bursting at the seams with fresh, sweet hop aromas. Pine, malt, and bready undertones are all there too, but the fresh hops exhibited here are unmatched by any APA.
T: I don't like most APAs. I dislike hoppy beer in general, but this is incredibly good. Taste is full of hops, bitterness is kept in check by the strong malt backbone. Slightly sweet through the middle, then fades mildly bitter to finish dry. Best of style; superb!
