4.64/5  rDev +2.4%look: 4 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5Big thanks to Fantasyroach for kicking in a brace of these 12oz bottles as extras in a recent trade. Drunk as quick as possible. Great artwork, no bottled-on date that I can see.
A. Deep dull copper orange. Beauteous tight foamy head, big lacing... nothing wrong here.
S. Great mother of hop cones! Supremely "right on" nose... bold bright Citra hops, bucketloads, nay, TRUCKLOADS of tangerine, mandarin orange, peach candy, sweet sticky malt, a touch of kumquat, tropical! smooth, candy-like... and yet, you know there are real hops here.
T. Oh heavens... sweet, succulent, soft, creamy, marriage of hops & grain sugars, yet not syrupy or cloying. Everything here just blends so much into the other that the fruity hops and sugar-kissed malt are the same flavor. Citra delight. I don't know what magic FFF has worked here, but it goes together so well that it is immediately iconic. I hate sounding like a shill, but there it is.
M / D. Thick, creamy, soft. Powder-dry finish, but until then, this is simply so soft and silly to drink as to be delightful; it practically gallops down your throat. Could be a touch less dry, maybe? There is a (very) minor metallic note here that only bears mentioning because you have to find fault somewhere. You can drink Zombie Dust all day. I sure would... the finish is a minor mirror of the flavor, but isn't too bitter, or sweet, but just fades... away.
Dark Lord bless Three Floyds. Sometimes their schtick of huge, malt forward beer doesn't really work for me, but this thing... is... great. Is this the best American Pale Ale? Too soon to say, surely, but Zombie Dust makes a compelling case. Ugh, what am I going to do with my remaining one? 1,691 characterskkipple, Oct 22, 2011
