4.5/5  rDev -0.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5It's hard to say anything bad about this beer. I think it's world class in almost every way. When I think about a beer I could drink everyday, this is it. It pours a golden, near orange color with delicate carbonation bubbles and a sufficient head. The aroma is intoxicating, due to grapefruit and other citrus notes rather than alcohol. 
The taste has just the right amount of everything. It's hoppy enough to let you know care went into the hop profile yet sweet and slightly earthy at the same time. The citrus from the nose doesn't betray the palate. I wouldn't call it rich but rather drinkable. I could certainly make a six pack enjoyably last through a full sunday of football. I haven't had many APAs and maybe this is setting the bar high but the balance is exactly what I wish I found in more IPAs. 809 charactersrobboyd, Oct 13, 2011
4.92/5  rDev +8.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5This is like the tenth time I've drank Zombie Dust but only the first time that my pallet/brain have been unfried enough to give it a proper evaluation. 
I poured it and made a gross little noise, like a dude in gay porn. Then I smelled and made another gross noise, although it was less gross because it was louder and less nebbishy. Then I tasted it and flat out moaned, like a female porn star, and that shit's hot because it's something a woman would do.
There's nothing I can say, really, aside from that this is a damn near perfect APA. The hop profile is medium-strength citrus, the malt is of the perfect strength, and the aftertaste is a wonderful tang of alpha acids against the pleasant stultifaction of yeasty bread dough. It's one of those truly great sessionable beers, like Masala Mama or Red Racer, that exceeds the sum of its parts because it so perfectly balanced. 
 L-let this be a lesson to all you kids out there: if you're gonna review a beer, do it right. The first few times I had this I thought it was real good, but I was in no state to pass final judgment. 1,086 charactersmynie, Oct 12, 2011
