4.42/5  rDev -2.4%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5On tap at a FFF tap takeover at the University of Chicago Pub, 12 May 2011.
This pours a nice looking pale gold with a small white head that dies leaving a little lace. On the nose, it feels like shoving a freshly peeled orange skin into one's sinuses. It's a gigantic citrus hit, totally fresh, totally refreshing. In the mouth there is more of the same, not really a lack of a malt backbone because I didn't miss it, but just enough to provide a frame for some intense peeled citrus. The orange takes center stage and if there is much else, I missed it while enjoying the orange so much. The body is medium light and there is a long finish, striking a good balance between being interesting enough to drink but not too overwhelming to drink again, and again, and again.
Overall, this is an absolutely amazing brew. For me it blows Alpha King out of the water. The citra hops are just so vivid here with little to get in their way, but it's never unbalanced. A great, great beer. Please bottle soon. 1,002 charactersEricCioe, May 13, 2011
