4.3/5  rDev -5.1%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5Zombie Dust (awesome name) pours a pale, slightly cloudy yellow color with a beige head. The slick looking head melts slowly into the beer and leaves quite nice lace. It has a slightly cloudy look to it that is especially evident when compared to my fellow BA's Cortez.
The aroma is very fresh and bright with a load of sweet orange, white grapefruit and pineapple. There is also a little bit of fairly neutral sweetness and... well, really not much else. Citra hops are the main player in the aroma.
The flavor is more complex than I had imagined. Along with the fresh citrus hops described in the aroma, there is a very nice cracker like malt sweetness with a bit of toastiness. The hoppyness has a dry peppery character and some white grapefruit that mingle well with yeasty flavors that manifest themselves half way through each sip.
The mouthfeel is between medium and light with a finish that is very dry, but not aggressive like some super hoppy APAs. The finish leaves plenty of citrusy flavors on my pallet.
This is definitely a crushable (makes beer chugging gesture) beer that I am now really regretting that I did not get a growler of. I found it to be very similar to some of the super hoppy west coast APAs that I have tried, but with just enough of that more balanced Midwest feel to make it that much more enjoyable. 1,336 characterszoso1967, Feb 21, 2011
