4.32/5  rDev -4.6%look: 3.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 3.5 |  overall: 5Huge thanks to glazeman for heading out to FFF this afternoon to pick up a growler of this and Hells Black Intelligentsia. Really looking forward to this brew. 
A - Appears amber and filtered (non-hazy) with a nice two finger head. Pretty standard appearance for an IPA or APA.
S - Incredible. Fresh, juicy, citrus hops. Not much else, but not much else is needed. 
T - This is just outstanding. A perfect combination of citrus and piney hops through out - sustained from the start to the finish. Tastes like a mixture between the biscuittiness of Gumballhead and the sharp hops of Alpha King. 
M - Appropriate for the style. Moderately carbonated with just a touch of thick elixir. 
D - Here is where this one shines. Crisp, fresh, and very easy to drink. This might just be the most drinkable beer I've ever had from FFF. I could easily knock off three pints on my own, maybe even an entire growler if I was feeling ambitious. I'm sure this one will become available in bombers. At least I hope it will... 1,012 charactersairohead2001, Dec 09, 2010
4.31/5  rDev -4.9%look: 4.5 | smell: 3.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5I had this on-tap at three floyds today, loved it, and decided to get a growler to bring home. This review is based on the growler.
A: Perfectly translucent and orange in color. There's a fluffy 1 finger off-white head that has moderate retention and excellent lacing. 
S: Not a very strong smelling beer, but very good smelling. There's floral/fruity notes and some acidity on the nose.
T: I absolutely love the hop profile in this beer. I haven't had any of the other beers that are made exclusively with citra hops, but this stuff is amazing. There's a bit of semi-sweet grapefruit up frunit, then some orange in the middle and the finish if of bitterness and earthiness at the finish.
M: Perfect. Nice carbonation, good viscosity, and a great aftertaste.
D: Fairly high, although the earthy/bitter aftertaste may get to be a bit much after a second glass. Still, there is great balance in this beer. Overall though, I was very impressed with this beer. In fact, I had it alongside daisy cutter and it blew daisy cutter out of the water in my opinion. 1,059 charactersglazeman, Dec 09, 2010
